Sentencas: A high-performance solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) single cell with La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-delta (LSGM) thin film (5 mu m thick) as electrolyte, working at 400-700 degrees C, was demonstrated.
Titulo: High-power SOFC using La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-δ/Ce0.8Sm0.2O2-δ composite film

Sentencas: A Ce0.8Sm0.2O2-delta (SDC) interlayer (400 nm thick) was introduced between the anode substrate of NiO-Fe2O3-SDC and the LSGM thin film to prohibit the reaction between LSGM and NiO and also to promote the electrode processes.
Titulo: High-power SOFC using La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-δ/Ce0.8Sm0.2O2-δ composite film

Sentencas: Both SDC and LSGM films were deposited by pulsed laser deposition.
Titulo: High-power SOFC using La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-δ/Ce0.8Sm0.2O2-δ composite film

Sentencas: The peak power density reached 3270, 1951, 612, and 80 mW/cm(2) at 700, 600, 500, and 400 degrees C, respectively, which may broaden the SOFC application to the mobile field.
Titulo: High-power SOFC using La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-δ/Ce0.8Sm0.2O2-δ composite film
